Build Genivi 7.0.3 p1 with Wayland IVI Extension
=====================================================

1. Source oe-init-build-env

	source oe-init-build-env

2. Add meta-fsl-ivi layer dependency paths to COREBASE/build/conf/bblayers.conf
   in BBLAYERS variable.

3. Set MACHINE ?= "imx6qsabreauto" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf

4. Add INCOMPATIBLE_LICENSE = "GPLv3" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf file.

5. Set DISTRO ?= "poky-ivi-systemd" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf file.

6. Accept End User License Agrement to use prebuilt GPU binaries
   add in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf

	ACCEPT_FSL_EULA = "1"

7. Build ivi-image-demo including GENIVI 7.0.3 P1 components and Wayland backend

	bitbake ivi-image-demo

Running Wayland test applications
=====================================================

1. Deploy rootfs image into and sdcard

	sudo dd if=intrepid-image-imx6qsabreauto.sdcard of=/dev/SDxx && sync && sync

2. Place SD on imx6sabreauto and power on

3. Run test application
